    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Proverbs",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 26,
        "summary": "Honor is not fitting for a fool\u2014Answer not a fool according to his folly\u2014Where there is no talebearer, the strife ceases.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "As snow in summer, and as rain in harvest, so honour is not seemly for a fool.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 12:9; D&C 121:35.",
                        "start": 46,
                        "end": 52
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "As the bird by wandering, as the swallow by flying, so the curse causeless shall not come.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A whip for the horse, a bridle for the ass, and a rod for the fool's back.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Answer not a fool according to his folly, lest thou also be like unto him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Answer a fool according to his folly, lest he be wise in his own conceit.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Matt. 16:2 (1\u20134).",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 6
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0own eyes (also vv.\u00a012, 16).",
                        "start": 61,
                        "end": 72
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "He that sendeth a message by the hand of a fool cutteth off the feet, and drinketh damage.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "OR\u00a0violence, injury.",
                        "start": 83,
                        "end": 89
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 70,
                        "end": 73
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The legs of the lame are not equal: so is a parable in the mouth of fools.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 41
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As he that bindeth a stone in a sling, so is he that giveth honour to a fool.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As a thorn goeth up into the hand of a drunkard, so is a parable in the mouth of fools.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The great God that formed all things both rewardeth the fool, and rewardeth transgressors.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Reward.",
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 13
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As a dog returneth to his vomit, so a fool returneth to his folly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Pet. 2:22; 3\u00a0Ne. 7:8.",
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 31
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Seest thou a man wise in his own conceit? there is more hope of a fool than of him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Rom. 11:25; 12:16.",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 29:20.",
                        "start": 66,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 42,
                        "end": 50
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The slothful man saith, There is a lion in the way; a lion is in the streets.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Laziness.",
                        "start": 4,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 24,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As the door turneth upon his hinges, so doth the slothful upon his bed.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 40,
                        "end": 44
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The slothful hideth his hand in his bosom; it grieveth him to bring it again to his mouth.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 35
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The sluggard is wiser in his own conceit than seven men that can render a reason.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 13,
                        "end": 15
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that passeth by, and meddleth with strife belonging not to him, is like one that taketh a dog by the ears.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Dogs were not pets in Israel, but typically ran wild; one seized by the ears would certainly bite its attacker.",
                        "start": 84,
                        "end": 90
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 20,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 45,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 67,
                        "end": 74
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As a mad man who casteth firebrands, arrows, and death,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 12
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "So is the man that deceiveth his neighbour, and saith, Am not I in sport?",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "D&C 10:25 (25\u201328).",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 28
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 3,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 18
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Where no wood is, there the fire goeth out: so where there is no talebearer, the strife ceaseth.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip.",
                        "start": 65,
                        "end": 75
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 4:9 (8\u20139); 16:18.",
                        "start": 81,
                        "end": 87
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 53,
                        "end": 61
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As coals are to burning coals, and wood to fire; so is a contentious man to kindle strife.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Contention.",
                        "start": 57,
                        "end": 68
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 2
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 9,
                        "end": 12
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The words of a talebearer are as wounds, and they go down into the innermost parts of the belly.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 26,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Burning lips and a wicked heart are like a potsherd covered with silver dross.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0a broken piece of an earthen vessel.",
                        "start": 43,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 32,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "He that hateth dissembleth with his lips, and layeth up deceit within him;",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hate.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 14
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Deceit.",
                        "start": 56,
                        "end": 62
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "When he speaketh fair, believe him not: for there are seven abominations in his heart.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ps. 28:3; Isa. 9:17.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 44,
                        "end": 53
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whose hatred is covered by deceit, his wickedness shall be shewed before the whole congregation.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Alma 14:3 (2\u20133); 37:21.",
                        "start": 59,
                        "end": 65
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 77,
                        "end": 82
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Whoso diggeth a pit shall fall therein: and he that rolleth a stone, it will return upon him.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 28:10; 1\u00a0Ne. 14:3; 22:14; 2\u00a0Ne. 28:8; D&C 109:25.",
                        "start": 16,
                        "end": 19
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "A lying tongue hateth those that are afflicted by it; and a flattering mouth worketh ruin.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Gossip.",
                        "start": 2,
                        "end": 7
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Flatter.",
                        "start": 60,
                        "end": 70
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 22,
                        "end": 36
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}